Emotional send off for slain Syombua, two children as relatives cry for justice             Philip Muasya  08th Dec 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Philip Muasya  08th Dec 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Philip Muasya   Caskets bearing the remains of Joyce Syombua and her two children Shanice Maua (10) and Prince Michael (5) at Kyeithani village, Kitui Rural, Kitui County where they were buried on December 7, 2019. The three were found murdered and buried in a shallow grave on November 16, three weeks after visiting Major Peter Mugure of Laikipia Airbase. [Philip Muasya, Standard]  Caskets bearing the remains of Joyce Syombua and her two children Shanice Maua (10) and Prince Michael (5) at Kyeithani village, Kitui Rural, Kitui County where they were buried on December 7, 2019. The three were found murdered and buried in a shallow grave on November 16, three weeks after visiting Major Peter Mugure of Laikipia Airbase. [Philip Muasya, Standard] Caskets bearing the remains of Joyce Syombua and her two children Shanice Maua (10) and Prince Michael (5) at Kyeithani village, Kitui Rural, Kitui County where they were buried on December 7, 2019. The three were found murdered and buried in a shallow grave on November 16, three weeks after visiting Major Peter Mugure of Laikipia Airbase. [Philip Muasya, Standard] Caskets bearing the remains of Joyce Syombua and her two children Shanice Maua (10) and Prince Michael (5) at Kyeithani village, Kitui Rural, Kitui County where they were buried on December 7, 2019. The three were found murdered and buried in a shallow grave on November 16, three weeks after visiting Major Peter Mugure of Laikipia Airbase.      SEE ALSO :Mother, children found buried in shallow grave SEE ALSO : Mother, children found buried in shallow grave        For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.       SEE ALSO :Major Peter Mugure detained for 21 days over murde